    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-07-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-07-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Marsh</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 135.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-07-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 24, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of June 29, No. 123, has
                            been received. I thank you for the interesting information which it
                            communicates. It is not deemed important that you should make at present
                            any proposition to the Italian government relative to the negotiation of
                            a consular convention. You will, therefore, confine yourself, under the
                            authority that has already been given you, to the negotiation of a
                            commercial treaty.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George P. Marsh,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Florence.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
